(78, 'WHAT IS THE NAME OF PYTHON\'S BUILT IN MODULE FOR EMAIL RELATED TASKS ', 'what-is-the-name-of-python-s-built-in-module-for-email-related-tasks', 'The smtplib module defines an SMTP client session object that can be used to send mail to any Internet machine with an SMTP', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><font color=\"#222222\" face=\"source sans pro, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, segoe ui, Roboto, helvetica neue, Arial, sans-serif, apple color emoji, segoe ui emoji, segoe ui symbol\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">This post describes all available builtin module of python for sending , recieving mails. Maybe you need to get email updates from your code, send an confirmation email to clients when they make a record, or send messages to individuals from your team to remind them to take care of their stuff. Sending messages physically is a tedious and solemn assignment, yet it\'s not difficult to robotize with Python.</span></font></p><h2><font color=\"#222222\" face=\"source sans pro, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, segoe ui, Roboto, helvetica neue, Arial, sans-serif, apple color emoji, segoe ui emoji, segoe ui symbol\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">There are totally 7 types of Built-In Module present in python for email Services.</span></font></h2><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\">Â·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Module smtplib<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">SMTP (Simple Mail Transport Protocol)\r\nclient</p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\">Â·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Module email â€” An email and MIME handling\r\npackage<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\">Â·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Module poplib</p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">POP (Post Office Protocol) client<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\">Â·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Module imaplib<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">IMAP (Internet Message Access Protocol)\r\nclient<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\">Â·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Module nntplib</p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">NNTP (Net News Transport Protocol) client<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\">Â·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Module mailbox<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">Tools for creating, reading, and managing\r\ncollections of messages on disk using a variety standard formats.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-family:\r\nSymbol\">Â·<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â \r\n</span></span><!--[endif]-->Module smtpd<o:p></o:p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">SMTP server framework (primarily useful for\r\ntesting)</p><h2><span style=\"font-size:24.0pt;line-height:115%\">Email â€” An\r\nemail and MIME handling package</span></h2><p class=\"MsoNormal\">The email package is a library for managing email messages.\r\nIt is specifically not designed to do any sending of email messages to SMTP or\r\nother servers. The overall structure of the email package can be divided\r\ninto three major component.</p><p><span style=\"font-size:24.0pt;line-height:115%\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">The central component of the package is an â€œobject modelâ€\r\nthat represents email messages. The other two major components of the package\r\nare the parser and the generator. The parser takes the serialized version of an\r\nemail message (a stream of bytes) and converts it into a tree of Email Message\r\nobjects. The generator takes an Email Message and turns it back into a serialized\r\nbyte stream.</p><h2><span style=\"font-size:24.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%\">Smtplib â€” SMTP protocol client</span></h2><p><span style=\"font-size:24.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%\"></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">The smtplib module defines an SMTP client session object\r\nthat can be used to send mail to any Internet machine with an SMTP.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>Example :Â </b></p><pre><p class=\"MsoNormal\">import smtplib</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">def prompt(prompt):<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">return input(prompt).strip()<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">fromaddr = prompt(\"From: \")</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">toaddrsÂ  =\r\nprompt(\"To: \").split()</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">print(\"Enter message, end with ^D (Unix) or ^Z\r\n(Windows):\")</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"># Add the From: and To: headers at the start!</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">msg = (\"From: %s\\r\\nTo: %s\\r\\n\\r\\n\"</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Â Â Â Â Â Â  % (fromaddr,\r\n\", \".join(toaddrs)))</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">while True:</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Â Â Â  try:<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Â Â Â Â  line = input()</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Â Â Â  except EOFError:</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  break</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Â Â Â  if not line:</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  break</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Â Â Â  msg = msg + line</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">print(\"Message length is\", len(msg))</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">server = smtplib.SMTP(\'localhost\')</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">server.set_debuglevel(1)</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">server.sendmail(fromaddr, toaddrs, msg)</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">server.quit()</p><p><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 22pt; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: 22pt; text-indent: -0.25in; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">poplib â€” POP3 protocol client</span><br></p></pre><p>\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(32, 33, 36); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">POP3</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(32, 33, 36); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Â (Post Office Protocol 3) is the most used version of a\r\nstandard protocol for receiving e-mail.Â <b>POP3</b>Â is a\r\nclient/server protocol in which e-mail is received and accessed by server.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 13.5pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(32, 33, 36); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b>Example :Â </b></span></p><pre><span style=\"line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><o:p style=\"\"><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"\"><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">import getpass, poplib\r\n</span></font></p><p><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">\r\n</span></font><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">M = poplib.POP3(\'localhost\')</span></font></p><p><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">M.user(getpass.getuser())</span></font></p><p><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">M.pass_(getpass.getpass())</span></font></p><p><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">numMessages = len(M.list()[1])</span></font></p><p><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">for i in range(numMessages):</span></font></p><p><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">    for j in M.retr(i+1)[1]:</span></font></p><p><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"><br></span></font><font color=\"#202124\" face=\"Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">        print(j)</span></font></p><p></p></o:p></span></pre>\r\n<h2><span style=\"font-size:22.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%\">Conclusion :Â </span></h2><p><span style=\"font-size:22.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%\"></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;line-height:115%\">So you can\r\nuse above python built-in module to receive , send , retrieve mail .But at last\r\nI also want share that security is another important thing. So using ssl module\r\nand securing connection is recommended on real world project .<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '2021-04-10 14:46:36', 'coding , python , email ,', '13', 'pythonsmtp.jpg', ''),
(79, 'What is Operating System? List of operating system , working and features.', 'what-is-operating-system-list-of-operating-system-working-and-features', 'AN operating system is an software or a program that connects hardware and user simultaneously with each other to share there responses.', '<h2>What is OS(Operating System).</h2>\r\n<p>An Operating System (OS) is a System software that work as an medium or we can say an interface between PC equipment segments (hardware ) and the client user . Applications software like Browsers, MS Office, Notepad Games, and so forth, need some climate to run and play out its assignments. This need is fulfilled by operating system.</p>\r\n<p>Nowadays in market there are lot of operating system is present. But mostly Some of them is most popular. Some example of os is - Windows , Linux , MacOS , ubuntu etc.  And we already know that Window is mostly used one of them.</p>\r\n<h2>Types of Operating System .</h2>\r\n<p>Some widely used operating systems are as follows- </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li ><a href= \"#tp1\">Batch Operating System</a>\r\n<li><a href=\"#tp2\">Time-Sharing Operating Systems/ Multi -Tasking OS</a>\r\n<li><a href =\"#tp3\">Distributed Operating System </a>\r\n<li><a href=\"#tp4\">Real-Time Operating System</a>\r\n<li><a href=\"#tp5\">Network Operating System </a>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 id = \"tp1\">Batch Operating System</h3>\r\n<p>A Computer have to perform many work . Doing all of these become messy Sometime . That`s Why batch operating System comes. In this operating System all similar type of job for cpu is sorted and group them as Batch.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"tp2\">Multi -Tasking Operating System</h3>\r\n<p>On Using computer we came around doing multiple task at a time . Like playing Music , Web Browsing , or Writing something on text editor . Doing multiple work is at once is example of multitasking Operating system . </p>\r\n<h3 id=\"tp3\">Distributed Operating System</h3>\r\n<p>Distributed Operating System is operating system which is installed on a computer and that computer is connected through network and anyone have access to that network can use this os. Remote access is enabled within the devices connected in that network. </p>\r\n<h3 id=\"tp4\">Real-Time Operating System</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nThe time interval required to process and respond to inputs is very small. This time interval is called response time. \r\nThese are used in \r\nrobots , Missile , Rockts etc.</p>\r\n<h3 id = \"tp5\">Network Operating System</h3>\r\n<p>Network Operating System runs on a Web server. For example : apache server , Microsoft server etc</p>\r\n<h2>Conclusion : </h2>\r\n<p>An Operating System (OS) is a System software that work as an medium or we can say an interface between PC equipment segments (hardware ) and the client user.</p>\r\n\r\n', '2021-04-14 01:41:36', '`Computer', '13', 'what-is-operating-system.png', ''),
