(85, 'HTTP status codes', 'http-status-codes', 'we can say HTTP response status codes indicate whether a specific HTTP request has been successfully completed or something went wrong.', '<p>When a client (ie. user with browser) request a server to get some content then a three digit number as a response is provided by server thats describes the status of request.\r\n    this three digit code is HTTP status code.\r\n    One of the famous <strong> 404 </strong>http status code (Page not found) is absolutely faced by you.\r\n</p>\r\n<img class=\"imga\" src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/85/HTTP status codes.jpg\" alt=\"http error code\">\r\n<h2>why http status codes? </h2>\r\n<p>when requesting some content from server it is very iportant to check if the request was succesfully completed or something went wrong on serverside or at clientside. so the http status code is introduced that gives you information about the status of your current request with specific three digit status code . \r\n    </p>\r\n<p>So we can say HTTP response status codes indicate whether a specific HTTP request has been successfully completed or something went wrong.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>list of http status codes</h2>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <h4><a href=\"#\"> 1xx - Informational</a></h4>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <h4><a href=\"#\"> 2xx - Success</a></h4>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <h4><a href=\"#\"> 3xx - Redirection</a></h4>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <h4><a href=\"#\">4xx - Client error</a> </h4>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>\r\n        <h4><a href=\"#\">5xx - Server error </a> </h4>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <p>check out  <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_HTTP_status_codes\">wikipedia</a> for more.</p>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.iana.org/assignments/http-status-codes/http-status-codes.xhtml\"> Internet Assigned Numbers Authority </a>(IANA) maintains the official registry of HTTP status codes.</p>\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>HTTP status code specifies the status code of current request. please go with link above to get more information about individual detail of every http status codes.</p>\r\n    \r\n\r\n\r\n', '2021-08-25 06:09:07', 'http status codes ,list of http, status codes, common http, status codes, http status codes 302, http status codes list', '13', 'http-368146_640.jpg', 'HTTP status codes.jpg/'),
(86, 'http 100 continue', 'http-100-continue', 'http 100 continue Status code is an informational response indicates that the request was received and client', '<p>Status code 100 is an informational response indicates that the request was received and client can continue to send their message body. </p>\r\n<h2>What is 100 Status code</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/86/100continue.png\" alt=\"100 continue image\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>Http Status code 1XX is about information and status of current request. \r\n    In Which 100 Continue header says that you can continue with your current request to send large body to server for example a POST request.\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>100 : Continue </h2>\r\n<p>Lets take an example to clear it .</p>\r\n<p> For example, a request that begins with\r\n\r\n    PUT /somewhere/fun HTTP/1.1\r\n    Host: origin.example.com\r\n    Content-Type: video/h264\r\n    Content-Length: 1234567890987\r\n    Expect: 100-continue\r\n</p>\r\n<p>If Client want to send this request (a large message body )then we have to send expect 100 continue Expectation header to server and in response to this server will send 100 Continue and we can continue sending message body.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If a client that receives a 417 (Expectation Failed) status code in\r\n    response to a request containing a 100-continue expectation SHOULD\r\n    repeat that request without a 100-continue expectation, because 417 response code suggest that server does not support expectation.</p>\r\n<h3>Requirements for clients:</h3>\r\n<p>Client cannot send 100 continue expectation in which their is no message body.</p>\r\n<p>A client that will wait for a 100 (Continue) response before\r\n    sending the request message body MUST send an Expect header field\r\n    containing a 100-continue expectation.</p>\r\n<p>A client that sends a 100-continue expectation withot Except header field is not required to\r\n    wait for any  length of time, such a client MAY continue to\r\n    send the message body even if it has not yet received a response.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Requirements for servers:</h3>\r\n<p>A server that receives a 100-continue expectation in an HTTP/1.0\r\n    request MUST ignore that expectation.\r\n    because HTTP/1.0 does not support expectation.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n<p>A server MAY omit sending a 100 (Continue) response if it has\r\n    already received some or all of the message body for the\r\n    corresponding request.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7231#section-5.1.1\">For more click here.</a></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>So 100 continue is a informational header that tells client to continue with current request.</p>\r\n', '2021-09-06 10:36:11', 'http status code', '13', '100continue.png', ''),
(87, 'Http 101 Switching Protocols', 'http-101-switching-protocols', ' This 101 status code is send by server when server understand and switching to newer version of Http on client\'s\r\n request.', '<p>Status code 101 is an informational response indicates that the Client request for changing protocol is accepted.</p>\r\n<h2>What is 101 Status code</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/87/101switchingprotocol.png\" alt=\"101 switching protocol\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>Http Status code 1XX is about information and status of current request.\r\n    This 101 status code is send by server when server understand and switching to newer version of Http on client\'s\r\n    request.\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>101 : Switching Protocol</h2>\r\n<p>Lets take an example to clear it .</p>\r\n<p> For example The client has to be send a request to server with Upgrade header field to switch protocol . A client\r\n    MAY send a list of protocols in the Upgrade\r\n    header field of a request to invite the server to switch to one or\r\n    more of those protocols.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>It is assumed that the server will only agree to switch protocols\r\n    when it is advantageous to do so . A server MAY ignore a received Upgrade\r\n    header field if it wishes to continue using the current protocol on\r\n    that connection.</p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Server must send Upgrade header field in the response that indicates\r\n    which protocol(s) will be switched immediately.</p>\r\n<p>Some server may send 426 (Upgrade Required) response that is because of the server does not support the protocol in which the client has requested to switch . In Response Server MUST send an\r\n    Upgrade header field to indicate the acceptable protocols, in order\r\n    of descending preference.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> If a server receives both an Upgrade and an Expect header field with\r\n    the \"100-continue\" expectation.Then the\r\n    server MUST send a 100 (Continue) response before sending a 101\r\n    (Switching Protocols) response.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7231#section-6.2.2\">For more click here.</a></p>\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p> This 101 status code is send by server when server understand and switching to newer version of Http on client\'s\r\n    request.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very Important for us.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '2021-09-07 10:04:58', 'http status code', '13', '101switchingprotocol.png', ''),
(88, 'Http Status 102 Processing ', 'http-status-102-processing', 'This 102 status code is send by server when server is working on client request but no result is available yet .... know more...', '<p>Status code 102 is an informational response indicates that the Client request was accepted by server and it is under process.</p>\r\n<h2>What is 102 Status code</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/88/httpstatus102Processings.png\" alt=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/88/httpstatus102Processings.png\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>Http Status code 1XX is about information and status of current request.\r\n    This 102 status code Processing shows that server is processing the client request but there is no result available at this moment.\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>102 : Processing</h2>\r\n<p>Sometime server may be busy due to havy load or the request is taking time to complete. so to prevents the client from timing out and assuming the request was lost. </p>\r\n<p>Lets take an example to clear it .</p>\r\n<p> For example The client has sent a request to server but the server is taking longer to give result .In the mean client may get timeout and think that request is lost . So to avoid this problem server shows Proceessing status code .\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p> This 102 status code is send by server when server is working on client request but no result is available yet .</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very Important for us.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n', '2021-09-08 09:34:59', 'http status code', '13', 'httpstatus102Processings.png', ''),
(89, 'http 103 Early Hints', 'http-103-early-hints', 'Http Status code 1XX is about information. In which 103 status code is send by server to client while server is\r\nProcessing about final response.', '<p>Status code 103 is an informational response. Used to return some response headers before final HTTP response 200 ok\r\n    from server.</p>\r\n<h2>What is 103 Status code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/89/http-103-EarlyHints-min.png\" alt=\"http 103 Early Hints\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>Http Status code 1XX is about information. In which 103 status code is send by server to client while server is\r\n    Processing about final response.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>103 : Early Hints</h2>\r\n\r\n<p> It is common for <a href=\"https://qnastop.com/http-status-codes\">HTTP Response</a> to contain links to external\r\n    resources that need to be fetched prior to their use, for example,\r\n    rendering HTML by a web browser. Having such links available to the\r\n    client as early as possible helps to minimize perceived latency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> However, it is\r\n    not always possible for an origin server to generate the final response immediately after receiving a request.</p>\r\n<p> A server can send the\r\n    informational response containing some of the header fields to help\r\n    the client start making preparations for processing the final\r\n    response by preloading the scripts.</p>\r\n<p> The \"preload\" [Preload] link relation can be used to convey such\r\n    links in the Link header field of an HTTP response.</p>\r\n<p>Early Hints is send by server is all about the preloading of assets that will used by HTML documents that will\r\n    available soon.</p>\r\n<p>For Example :\r\n</p>\r\n<img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/89/earlyhint-http-status-code..png\" alt=\"103 early hint status code.\" class=\"imga\">\r\n\r\n<p>In the above example client had sent a early hint request and server respond with two early hint response.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aside from performance optimizations, such evaluation of the 103\r\n    (Early Hints) response\'s header fields MUST NOT affect how the final\r\n    response is processed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> A client can evaluate the header fields included in a\r\n    103 (Early Hints) response while waiting for the final response. For\r\n    example, a client might recognize a Link header field value\r\n    containing the relation type \"preload\" and start fetching the target\r\n    resource. However, these header fields only provide hints to the\r\n    client; they do not replace the header fields on the final response.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> As is the case with any informational response, a server might emit\r\n    more than one 103 (Early Hints) response prior to sending a final\r\n    response. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p> This 103 status code is send by server when server is thinking and <a href=\"https://qnastop.com/http-status-102-processing\">processing</a> or fetching database about final\r\n    response that need to be send to preload assets that will used later in final response by server. </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-09 10:12:44', 'http status code', '13', 'http-103-EarlyHints-min.png', 'earlyhint-http-status-code..png/'),
(90, 'http 200 OK Status code', 'http-200-ok-status-code', 'The 200 (OK) status code indicates that the request has succeeded. A 200 response is cacheable .... know more', '\r\n<p>The 200 OK (Succesfull) Http Status code returned to Client after receiving, understanding, and accepting the client\r\n    request and passing all <a href = \"https://qnastop.com/http-100-continue\">1XX</a>and 3XX <a href=\"https://qnastop.com/http-status-codes\">status code.</a>  </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 200 Status code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/90/200-ok-successfull.png\" alt=\"http 200 Ok succesful http status code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The 200 (OK) status code indicates that the request has succeeded. A 200 response is cacheable by default; i.e.,\r\n    unless otherwise\r\n    indicated by the method definition.</p>\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>200 OK : Status code</h2>\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/90/http-status-code-200-ok.png\" alt=\"http status code 200 OK example\" class=\"imga\">\r\n\r\n<p> The actual response will depend on the request method used .Like Post request , Get request, Head and Trace .</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>HEAD: The headers are included in the response without any content in body.</li>\r\n    <li>POST: The result of the request that is transmitted in the message body.</li>\r\n    <li>GET: The resource has been fetched and is transmitted in the message body.</li>\r\n    <li>TRACE: The message body which contains the request message that received by the server.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p> This200 OK status code is send by server when request is completed .\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-10 09:46:45', 'http status code', '13', '200-ok-successfull.png', 'http-status-code-200-ok.png/'),
(91, 'http 201 Created Status Code', 'http-201-created-status-code', 'The HTTP 201 Created success status response code indicates that the request has succeeded and resulting in the\r\ncreation ....', '<p>The HTTP 201 Created success status response code indicates that the request has succeeded and resulting in the\r\n    creation of a new resource.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 201 Status code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/91/101-created-status-code.png\" alt=\"http 201 Created Status Code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The 201 (Created) status code indicates that the request has been\r\n    completed and new resources has been created as a result. This new resource sent after POST requests, or some PUT\r\n    requests. </p>\r\n\r\n<h2>201 : Created Status code</h2>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>After new resources has been created as a result.</p>\r\n<p>The primary resource created by the request is identified\r\n    by either a Location header field or by the effective request URI .</p>\r\n<p>The 201 response typically describes and links to the\r\n    resource(s) created.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p> This 201 OK Created is send by server when request is succeeded and new resource has been succesfully created.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-11 07:57:49', 'http status code', '13', '101-created-status-code.png', ''),
(92, 'http 202 Accepted Status Code', 'http-202-accepted-status-code', 'http 202 Accepted status code indicates that the request has been\r\naccepted for processing, but the processing has not been completed.', '<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 2XX Success status code, In which we\r\n    cover http 202 Accepted <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_HTTP_status_codes\">Status code</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is http 202 Accepted Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/92/http-202-accepted-status-code.png\" alt=\"http 202 Accepted Status Code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 202 (Accepted) status code indicates that the request has been\r\n    accepted for processing, but the processing has not been completed.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>202 : Accepted Status Code</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The 202 Accepted HyperText Transfer Protocol (HTTP) response status code indicates that the request has been accepted\r\n    for processing, but the processing has not been completed or processing may not have started yet or it might\r\n    be disallowed when processing actually takes place. </p>\r\n<p>There is no\r\n    facility in HTTP for re-sending a status code from an asynchronous\r\n    operation.</p>\r\n<p>It is intended for cases where another process or server handles the request, or for <a href=\"https://qnastop.com/what-is-operating-system-list-of-operating-system-working-and-features#tp1\">batch processing.</a> </p>\r\n\r\n<p> Its purpose is to\r\n    allow a server to accept a request for some other process (perhaps a\r\n    batch-oriented process that is only run once per day) without\r\n    requiring that the user agent\'s connection to the server persist\r\n    until the process is completed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe http 202 response is knowingly indistinctive. Its purpose is to\r\nallow a server to accept a request for some other process without\r\ntaking that the user connection to the server carry on\r\nuntil the process is completed. The representation transferred with this\r\nresponse ought to describe the request\'s current status and point to a status observer that can give the user with an\r\nestimate of when the request will be fulfilled.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7231#section-6.3.3\">202 accepted </a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The request has been accepted for processing, but the processing has not been completed.it might\r\n    be disallowed when processing actually takes place.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-12 07:58:51', 'http status code, http 202, Accepted Status Code', '13', 'http-202-accepted-status-code.png', ''),
(93, 'http 203 Non-Authoritative Information', 'http-203-non-authoritative-information', 'the 203 status code indicates that\r\nthe request was successful but the enclosed packet that received by client has been modified\r\nSome proxy.   ', '<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 2XX Success status code, In which we\r\n    cover 203 Non-Authoritative Information</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 203 Non-Authoritative Information ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/93/http-203-Non-Authoritative-Information-status-code.png\" alt=\"http 203 Non-Authoritative Information status Code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    The 203 (Non-Authoritative Information) status code indicates that\r\n    the request was successful but the enclosed payload has been modified\r\n    from that of the origin server\'s 200 (OK) response by a transforming\r\n    proxy.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>203 : Non-Authoritative Information</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The 203 (Non-Authoritative Information) status code indicates that\r\n    the request was successful but the enclosed packet by original server has been modified by some proxy.\r\n</p>\r\n<p> A 203 response is cacheable by default.</p>\r\n<p>This status code allows the\r\n    proxy to notify recipients when a transformation has been applied (214 warning code),\r\n    since that knowledge might impact later decisions regarding the\r\n    content. </p>\r\n<p> A proxy might, for example, convert between image\r\n    formats in order to save cache space or to reduce the amount of\r\n    traffic on a slow link. </p>\r\n<p>An HTTP-to-HTTP proxy is called a \"transforming proxy\" if it is\r\n    designed or configured to modify messages in a semantically\r\n    meaningful way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> However, operational problems might occur when integrity checks or digital signatures\r\n    are used to ensure that the payload received is identical to the\r\n    original.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>So the 203 status code indicates that\r\n    the request was successful but the enclosed packet that received by client has been modified\r\n    Some proxy.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-13 10:16:39', 'http status code', '13', 'http-203-Non-Authoritative-Information-status-code.png', '');
INSERT INTO `blog_article` (`article_id`, `article_title`, `article_slug`, `article_description`, `article_content`, `postedon`, `tags`, `category`, `post_img`, `article_image`) VALUES
(94, 'http 204 No Content status code', 'http-204-no-content-status-code', '    The HTTP 204 No Content success status response code indicates that a request has succeeded, But user agent does not\r\n    need to traverse away from its current document view. or we can say that user will not leave its current page.', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 2XX Success status code, In which we\r\n    cover 204 No Content Status Code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 204 No Content ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/94/http-204-No-Content-status-code.png\" alt=\"http-204-No-Content-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    The HTTP 204 No Content success status response code indicates that a request has succeeded, But user agent does not\r\n    need to traverse away from its current document view. or we can say that user will not leave its current page.</p>\r\n<p>The server successfully processed the request but not returning any content to client in response.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>204 : No Content </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The 204 (No Content) status code indicates that the server has\r\n    successfully fulfilled the request and that there is no additional\r\n    content to send in the response payload(packet) body.</p>\r\n<p>Generally, when a PUT request\r\n    modifies existing resource the server will return a 200 (OK) or 204 (No Content).</p>\r\n<p>  The 204 response allows a server to indicate that the action has been\r\n    successfully applied to the target resource.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The server assumes that the user agent will provide\r\n    some indication of the success to its user, in according with its own\r\n    interface.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a 204 status code is commonly used with document editing\r\n    interfaces Like wordpress editor where save action is used to save current document eithout loading your page for continue editing. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>  A 204 response is cacheable by default.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7231#section-6.3.5\">For more click here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>So we can that 204 no Content indicates that request is fulfilled but no additional content is sen in response.Generally it is an PUT request. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-14 13:44:37', 'http status code', '13', 'http-204-No-Content-status-code.png', ''),
(95, 'http 205 Reset Content status code', 'http-205-reset-content-status-code', ' The 205 (Reset Content) status code indicates that the server has\r\nfulfilled the request and and server wants to user agent to reset the....', '<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 2XX Success status code, In which we\r\n    cover 205 Reset Content  <a href=\"https://qnastop.com/http-status-codes\">Status Code</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 205 Reset Content ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/95/http-205-Reset-Content-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http 205 Reset Content status Code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    The 205 (Reset Content) status code indicates that the server has\r\n    <a href = \"https://qnastop.com/http-200-ok-status-code\">fulfilled the request </a>and and server wants to user agent to reset the\r\n    document view, such as input fields ot refresh the current page to its original\r\n    state as received from the origin server.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>205 : Reset Content </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In 205 No Content status code is sent to client when client receives content like foem notepad etc. and enters or\r\n    manipulates some data in it . and then a request is sent to submit data. </p>\r\n<p>Now we need to reset the page content to fill another data. so here 205 Reset Content status code is used.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    Since the 205 status code implies that no additional content will be\r\n    provided, a server MUST NOT generate a payload(packet) in a 205 response.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7231#section-6.3.6\">For more click here</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The 205 (Reset Content) status code indicates that the server has\r\n    fulfilled the request and desires that the user agent reset the\r\n    document view(page view)\r\n    .</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-21 08:28:41', 'http status code', '13', 'http-205-Reset-Content-status-code-min.png', ''),
(96, 'http-3XX-status-code', 'http-3xx-status-code', 'The 3xx (Redirection) class of status code indicates that some further\r\naction needs to be taken by the user agent in order to....', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 3XX REdirection status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 3xx Redirect ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/96/http-3XX-status-code-min (1).png\" loading = \"lazy\" alt=\"http-3xx-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p> The 3xx (Redirection) class of status code indicates that some further\r\n    action needs to be taken by the user agent in order to Complete the\r\n    request. If a Location header field is provided, the\r\n    user agent MAY automatically redirect its request to the URI\r\n    referenced by the Location field value, even if the specific status\r\n    code is not understood.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>3XX : Redirect</h2>\r\n<p>There are several type of Redirect :</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>300 Multiple Choices</li>\r\n    <li>301 Moved Permanently</li>\r\n    <li>302 Found </li>\r\n    <li>303 See Other</li>\r\n    <li>304 Not Modified </li>\r\n    <li>305 Use Proxy</li>\r\n    <li>306 Switch Proxy</li>\r\n    <li>307 Temporary Redirect </li>\r\n    <li>308 Permanent Redirect</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The 3XX Status indicates that the request is automatically redirected to some other uri that refrenced in location\r\n    header\r\n    .</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-22 08:35:31', 'http status code', '13', 'http-3XX-status-code-min (1).png', ''),
(97, 'http 300 Multiple Choices status code', 'http-300-multiple-choices-status-code', 'The 300 Multiple choice status code indicated that there more than one response is available and the user should have to choose....', '<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 3XX REdirection status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 300 Multiple Choices Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\" https://qnastop.com/upload/97/http-300-Multiple-Choices-status-code.png\" alt=\"http-300-multiple-choices-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p> The 300 Multiple choice status code indicated that there more than one response is available and the user should have to choose which one to display.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>300 : Multiple Choices</h2>\r\n<p>\r\nthis status code shows when user agent have option to choose from more than one possible response that is currently available.\r\n</p>\r\n<p> A 300 response is cacheable by default.</p>\\\r\n\r\n<p>by Default thier is no special option available for choosing between which response to load but some time html link were given to choose from. </p>\r\n<p>\r\n    For request methods, the server SHOULD generate a\r\n    payload(response) in the 300 response containing a list of representation\r\n    metadata and URI reference.(html) from which the user or user agent can\r\n    choose the one most preferred.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>If the server has a preferred choice, the server SHOULD generate a\r\n    Location header field containing a preferred choice\'s URI reference.</p>\r\n<p>For example :</p>\r\n<p>choosing quality of video while playing it .</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The 300 Status indicates that their is multiple response available and user should choose one of them to display\r\n    .</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-23 09:18:31', 'http status code', '13', 'http-300-Multiple-Choices-status-code.png', ''),
(98, 'http 301 Moved Permanently status code', 'http-301-moved-permanently-status-code', ' The 301 Moved Permanently status code indicates that the resource of this page is moved permanently to new uri(URL) . From now all resource.....', '<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 3XX REdirection status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 301 Moved Permanently Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/98/http-301-Moved-Permanently-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http-301-moved-permanently-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p> The 301 Moved Permanently status code indicates that the resource of this page is moved permanently to new uri(URL) . From now all resource will available through this new one Uri.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>300 : Multiple Choices</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n    Whenever we type a url in our browser then browser requests to server to get that page to display resource available for that url on our screen. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    But sometime our browser redirect us to another url that is different from our input url on the behalf of HEADER sent by server.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>This redirection means that the resources available to input url is permanently moved to new uri . and we can now use the new uri tto access the resource instead of using old uri.</p>\r\n<p>This 301 response is cacheable by default.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/98/http-301-Moved-Permanently-status-code.png\" alt=\"http-301-moved-permanently-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>So now we can say the server SHOULD generate a Location header field in the response\r\n    containing a preferred URI reference for the new permanent URI. </p>\r\n<p>The\r\n    user agent MAY use the Location field value for automatic\r\n    redirection to new uri.</p>\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The 300 Status indicates that the resouces to given url is no more and server will send a location header to automatically redirect you to another page with content\r\n    .</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-26 05:10:47', 'http status code', '13', 'http-301-Moved-Permanently-status-code-min.png', 'http-301-Moved-Permanently-status-code.png/'),
(99, 'http 302 Found status code', 'http-302-found-status-code', 'The HyperText Transfer Protocol (HTTP) 302 Found redirect status response code indicates that the resource requested has been temporarily...', '<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 3XX REdirection status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 302 Found Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/99/http-302-Found-status-code.png\" alt=\"http-302-Found-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p> The 302 (Found) status code indicates that the target resource\r\n    moved temporarily under a different URI by location header. </p>\r\n\r\n<h2>302 : Found</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n    The HyperText Transfer Protocol (HTTP) 302 Found redirect status response code indicates that the resource requested has been temporarily moved to the URI given by the Location header.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    \r\n   The server SHOULD generate a Location header field in the response\r\n   containing a URI reference for the different URI.  The user agent MAY\r\n   use the Location field value for automatic redirection.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The 302 (Found) status code indicates that the target resource\r\n    moved temporarily under a different URI by location header.\r\n    .</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-27 08:11:18', 'http status code', '13', 'http-302-Found-status-code.png', ''),
(100, 'http 303 See Other status code', 'http-303-see-other-status-code', 'The 303 (See Other) status code indicates that the server is\r\nredirecting the user agent to a different resource using.....', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 3XX REdirection status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 303 See Other Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/100/http-303-See-Other-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http-303-see-other-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>The 303 (See Other) status code indicates that the server is\r\n    redirecting the user agent to a different resource using get request.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>303 : See Other</h2>\r\n<p>the 303 redirect status code indicated thats after sending a post request to server, the client has to be redirected to another page that is using get request. </p>\r\n<p>instead of showing newly added resourse using post request.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>we can take an example to Understand :</p>\r\n<p>Think if we are uploading an image using post request but instead of showing this newly uploaded resource , server is redirecting user to a confirmation page using get request.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The 303 see other status code indicates  that it is primarily\r\n    used to allow the output of a POST action to redirect the user agent\r\n    to a selected resource\r\n    .</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-29 06:44:25', 'http status code', '13', 'http-303-See-Other-status-code-min.png', ''),
(101, 'http 307 Temporary Redirect status code', 'http-307-temporary-redirect-status-code', 'The 307 Temporary Redirect status code indicates that the target\r\nresource resides temporarily under a different URI...', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 3XX REdirection status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 307 Temporary Redirect Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/101/http-307-Temporary-Redirect-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http-307-temporary-redirect-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>  The 307 Temporary Redirect status code indicates that the target\r\n    resource resides temporarily under a different URI.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>307 : temporary redirect</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The 307 temporary redirect indicated that the requested resource is temporarily available under different url, ANd the user must not change request method that used primarily if there is an automatic redirection.</p>\r\n<p>Because this redirect is temporarily and this could be changed anytime, and the client have to use original uri to access the resource.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So in this case server should generate a location header that used by client for automatic redirection and payload generally contain an hypertext to that temporary uri.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> This status code is similar to <a href=\"https://qnastop.com/http-302-found-status-code\"> 302 (Found)</a>, except that it\r\n    does not allow changing the request method from POST to GET.So you may use <a href=\"https://qnastop.com/http-303-see-other-status-code\">303 \r\n    See Other </a> status code.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The 307 temporary redirect indicated that the requested resource is temporarily available under different url, ANd the user must not change request method from post to get.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-29 07:27:24', 'http status code', '13', 'http-307-Temporary-Redirect-status-code-min.png', ''),
(102, 'http 400 Bad Request status code', 'http-400-bad-request-status-code', 'the 400 Bad request status code indicates that server could not processed the request because something went wrong on client side while sending .', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 400 Bad Request Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/102/http-400-Bad-Request-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http-400-Bad-Request-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>the 400 Bad request status code indicates that server could not processed the request because something went wrong on client side while sending request.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>400 : Bad Request</h2>\r\n<p>In this case request will not be processed by server because of malformed request syntax, size too large, invalid request message framing, or deceptive request routing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now user will see an 400 status code page with bad request that something went wrong while sending requests.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>the 400 Bad request status code indicates that server could not processed the request because there is an error in sending request.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-30 04:16:30', 'http status code', '13', 'http-400-Bad-Request-status-code-min.png', ''),
(103, 'http 401 Unauthorized status code', 'http-401-unauthorized-status-code', 'The 401 Unauthorized status code indicates that the server understood\r\n    the request but refuses to authorize it....', '<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 401 Unauthorized Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/103/http-401-Unauthorized-status-code.png\" alt=\"http-401-Unauthorized-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p> The 401 Unauthorized status code indicates that the server understood\r\n    the request but refuses to authorize it because of invalid authentication crendentials.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>401 : Unauthorized</h2>\r\n<p>While sending request user lacks valid authentication data and request is processed by server but server refused to authorize it.</p>\r\n<p>In this case you may  have option to authorize it .</p>\r\n<p>This case is totally similar to <a href= \"/http-403-Forbidden-status-code\">403 Forbidden </a>but here authentication is posssible.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>So we can say user need valid authentication to access the resourse.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-09-30 04:43:59', 'http status code', '13', 'http-401-Unauthorized-status-code.png', ''),
(104, 'http 403 Forbidden status code', 'http-403-forbidden-status-code', '>While sending request user lacks valid authentication data and request is processed by server but server refused to authorize it.', '<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 403 Forbidden Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/104/http-403-Forbidden-status-code.png\" alt=\"http-403-Forbidden-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p> The 403 (Forbidden) status code indicates that the server understood\r\n    the request but refuses to authorize it.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>403 : Forbidden</h2>\r\n<p>While sending request user lacks valid authentication data and request is processed by server but server refused to authorize it.</p>\r\n<p>In this case you may not have option to to authorize it .</p>\r\n<p>This case is totally similar to <a href=\"https://qnastop.com/http-401-unauthorized-status-code\">401 Unauthorized</a>  but here no authentication is posssible.</p>\r\n<p> a server that wishes to\r\n    make public why the request has been forbidden can describe that\r\n    reason in the response payload (if any).</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>So we can say you need valid authentication to access the resourse.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '2021-09-30 04:54:30', 'http status code', '13', 'http-403-Forbidden-status-code.png', ''),
(105, 'http 404 Not Found status code', 'http-404-not-found-status-code', 'The 404 (Not Found) status code indicates that the origin server did\r\nnot find a resource for the target resource requested.', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 404 Not Found Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\" https://qnastop.com/upload/105/http-404 Not Found-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http-404 Not Found-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p> The 404 (Not Found) status code indicates that the origin server did\r\n    not find a resource for the target resource requested.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>404 : Not Found</h2>\r\n<p>The requested resource could not be found on server . This could be permanent or temporary</p>\r\n<p>  A 404 response is cacheable by default.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The HTTP 404 Not Found client error response code indicates that the server unable to find the requested resource.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '2021-10-01 04:39:00', 'http status code', '13', 'http-404 Not Found-status-code-min.png', ''),
(106, 'http 405 Method Not Allowed status code', 'http-405-method-not-allowed-status-code', 'The HyperText Transfer Protocol (HTTP) 405 Method Not Allowed response status code indicates that the targeted resource does not support the method', '\r\n\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 405 Method Not Allowed Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/106/Method-Not-Allowed-min.png\" alt=\"http-405 Method Not Allowed-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>The HyperText Transfer Protocol (HTTP) 405 Method Not Allowed response status code indicates that the targeted resource does not support the method you are using.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>405 : Method Not Allowed</h2>\r\n<p> In 405 method not allowed status code indicates that  method is known by server but the method used in this request is unsupported by the requested resource.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>the server must generate  Allow header field in a 405 response containing a list of currently supported methods.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> A 405 response is cacheable by default.</p>\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The HTTP  405 status code states that the method used in this request is unsupported by the requested resource.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '2021-10-01 05:01:39', 'http status code', '13', 'Method-Not-Allowed-min.png', ''),
(107, 'http 406 Not Acceptable status code', 'http-406-not-acceptable-status-code', 'THe HTTP 406 Not Acceptable client error status code indicates that the server is unable o produce the response that\r\n    is acceptable...', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 406 Not Acceptable Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/107/http-406-Not-Acceptable-status-code.png\" alt=\"http 406 Not Acceptable status code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>THe HTTP 406 Not Acceptable client error status code indicates that the server is unable o produce the response that\r\n    is acceptable by user agent.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>406 : Not Acceptable</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In this 406 status code server does not able to respond to user according to the Accept headers sent in the request.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>and the server\r\n    is unwilling to supply a default representation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The server should generate a list of available response for the corresponding resource so that user can choose one of\r\n    the most appropriate.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The HTTP 405 status code states that the response is unsupported by the user agent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-10-01 05:23:13', 'http status code', '13', 'http-406-Not-Acceptable-status-code.png', ''),
(108, 'http 408 Request Timeout status code', 'http-408-request-timeout-status-code', 'The 408 (Request Timeout) status code indicates that the server did\r\n    not receive a complete request message within the....', '\r\n\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 408 Request Timeout Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/108/http-408-Request-Timeout-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http-408-Request-Timeout-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p> The 408 (Request Timeout) status code indicates that the server did\r\n    not receive a complete request message within the maximum wait time.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>408 : Request Timeout</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    The HyperText Transfer Protocol  408 Request Timeout response status code means that the server would like to shut down this connection.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n    Because the maximum wait time is exceeded and now server Should send the \"close\" connection option\r\n    in the response.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>  If the client has an outstanding request in transit, the\r\n    client MAY repeat that request on a new connection.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The HTTP 408 Request Timeout status code states that the server has decided to close the connection rather than continue\r\n    waiting.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-10-02 06:20:38', 'http status code', '13', 'http-408-Request-Timeout-status-code-min.png', ''),
(109, 'http 409 Conflict status code', 'http-409-conflict-status-code', '  The 409 Conflict HTTP status code indicates that the request could not\r\n    be completed due to a conflict with the current state ....', '<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 409 Conflict  Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/109/Conflict-min.png\" alt=\"http-409-Conflict-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n    The 409 Conflict HTTP status code indicates that the request could not\r\n    be completed due to a conflict with the current state of the target\r\n    resource.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>409 : Conflict</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n    The 409 conflict occur generally when PUT request is used to update the resourse.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n   If version conrol is used and PUT request includes changes to resource that conflict with earlier update request.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>For example if you are using version control, and uploading the resource that already available on server with older version then server will respond with 409 conflict status code.</p>\r\n<p>This code is used in situations where the user might be\r\n    able to resolve the conflict and resubmit the request.</p>\r\n<p>The server\r\n    SHOULD generate a payload that includes enough information for a user\r\n    to recognize the source of the conflict.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The HTTP 409 Status Code indicates that server have some conflict with your current PUT request when uploading your file.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>\r\n\r\n', '2021-10-03 06:16:01', 'http status code', '13', 'Conflict-min.png', ''),
(110, 'http 410 Gone status code', 'http-410-gone-status-code', 'The 410 status code shows that target\r\nresource is unavailable at the origin server, and server dont...', '<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 410 Gone Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/110/http-410-Gone-status-code-min (1).png\" alt=\"http-410-Gone-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The 410 Gone Hyper Text Transfer Protocol status code indicates that access to the target\r\n    resource is no longer available at the origin server and this\r\n    condition is likely to be permanent. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2> 410 : Gone</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n    The 410 status code shows that target\r\n    resource is unavailable at the origin server, and server dont know if it is permanent or temporarily.\r\n</p>\r\n<p> If The resource unavailability is permanent, then status code 404 (Not Found) ought to be used\r\n    instead.</p>\r\n<p>This HTTP status Code is generally used when maintaining the web and to show user that resource is intentionally\r\n    unavailbale or the server owner want to remove the link for this resource.</p>\r\n<p>Such an event is common\r\n    for limited-time.</p>\r\n<p>A 410 response is cacheable by default.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The HTTP 410 Gone status code indicates that access to the target\r\n    resource is no longer available .</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-10-04 09:08:36', 'http status code', '13', 'http-410-Gone-status-code-min (1).png', ''),
(111, 'http 411 Length Required status code', 'http-411-length-required-status-code', ' The HTTP 411 Length Required status code indicates that the server\r\nrefuses to accept the request without a defined...', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 411 Length Required Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/111/Length-Required-min.png\" alt=\"http-411-Length-Required-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The HTTP 411 Length Required status code indicates that the server\r\n    refuses to accept the request without a defined Content-Length of message body.</p>\r\n\r\n    <p>The client must to add a valid Content-Length header field containing the length of\r\n        the message body in the request message.\r\n     </p>\r\n     <p>After adding Content length header field user agent may send the request again .</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The HTTP 411 indicates that the Content length of message body must be specified in request header field.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>\r\n', '2021-10-05 07:20:45', 'http status code', '13', 'Length-Required-min.png', ''),
(112, 'http 413 Payload Too Large status code', 'http-413-payload-too-large-status-code', 'The Hyper text transfer protocol 413 Payload Too Large status code indicates that the server is\r\nunable to process a request because the Requ...', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 413 Payload Too Large Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/112/http-413-Payload-Too-Large-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http-413-Payload-Too-Large-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The Hyper text transfer protocol 413 Payload Too Large status code indicates that the server is\r\n   unable to process a request because the Request entity is too large to handle.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>413 : Payload-Too-Large</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n    THe 413 Payload Too Large Status codes shows that payload(body) size is very large and it could not be processed by server .  \r\n</p>\r\n<p>Now the server close the connection to prevent continue request by user and return a Retry-After header field to user agent indicating the specified time after that user can try again to send request. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p>The HTTP 413 Payload too large status code indicates that the request entity is larger than limits defined by server and server continue to close the connection and return a Retry-After header field.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-10-05 07:45:56', 'http status code', '13', 'http-413-Payload-Too-Large-status-code-min.png', ''),
(113, 'http 414 URI Too Long status code', 'http-414-uri-too-long-status-code', 'The HTTP 414 URI Too Long status code indicates that the server is\r\n    refusing to service the request because the request-target is longer...', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 414 URI Too Long Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/113/http-414-URI-Too-Long-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http-414-URI-Too-Long-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p> The HTTP 414 URI Too Long status code indicates that the server is\r\n    refusing to service the request because the request-target is longer than the server is willing to interpret.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This rare condition is only likely to occur when a client has\r\n    improperly converted a POST request to a GET request with long query\r\n    information.</p>\r\n<p>when the server is under attack by a client attempting to\r\n    exploit potential security holes.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p> The HTTP 414 URI Too Long status code indicates that the server is\r\n   unable to process the request uri because it is longer than the expected.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-10-08 06:02:59', 'http status code', '13', 'http-414-URI-Too-Long-status-code-min.png', ''),
(114, 'http 415 Unsupported Media Type status code', 'http-415-unsupported-media-type-status-code', 'The HTTP status Code 415 Unsupported Media Type indicated that the origin server is refusing to complete the request because the payload....\r\n', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 415 Unsupported Media Type Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/114/http-415-Unsupported-Media-Type-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http-415-Unsupported-Media-Type-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The HTTP status Code 415 Unsupported Media Type indicated that the origin server is refusing to complete the request because the payload\r\n    is in a format not supported by the target resource.\r\n\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> The format problem might be due to the request\'s indicated\r\n    Content-Type or Content-Encoding,\r\n </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p> The HTTP 415 states that request could not be completed because of Unsupported Media type.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-10-09 03:52:56', 'http status code', '13', 'http-415-Unsupported-Media-Type-status-code-min.png', ''),
(115, 'http 426 Upgrade Required status code', 'http-426-upgrade-required-status-code', ' The HTTP 426 Upgrade Required client error status code indicates that the server not want to complete the request using the current protocol but....', '\r\n<p>http status code is send by server in response to client request. In which there are many type of http status code\r\n    like 1XX , 2XX, 3XX, 4XX, 5XX . In this Post we are going to talk about about 4XX Client Error status code.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is 426 Upgrade Required Status Code ?</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"https://qnastop.com/upload/115/http-426-Upgrade-Required-status-code-min.png\" alt=\"http-426-Upgrade-Required-status-code\" class=\"imga\"></p>\r\n<p>\r\n    The HTTP 426 Upgrade Required client error status code indicates that the server not want to complete the request using the current protocol but might be willing to do so after the client upgrades to a different protocol.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p> The server MUST send an Upgrade header field in a 426\r\n    response to indicate the required protocol.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\r\n<p> The HTTP 426 states that request could not be completed using current protocol.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class=\"fail\">If you find any error or want suggest some changes then <a href=\"/contact\">contact us now</a> It is very\r\n    Important for us.</p>', '2021-10-09 04:06:15', 'http status code', '13', 'http-426-Upgrade-Required-status-code-min.png', ''),
